Description: Fragment of double handle at neck join from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine micaceous beige; cream slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Zopyros. Unpublished parallel in Athenian Agora. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.110, 10. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0077)
